<p><span class="headers">August 17, 2002 - A Word of Warning</span>
<p>
<p><a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornernotesfromthedenmother.showMessage?topicID=1382.topic">It's
come to my attention</a> that one (or more) folks are sending out suspect file
attachments and spoofing the sender id to niami@eqtraders.com. If you receive
such an email, DO NOT download the file attachment. <b>It is not from me. I have
never, and will never send out email using that email address</b>. Look VERY
carefully at the email headers and return path, and it's likely that you can
find the true source of the email. I recommend that <i>if</i> you're
internet-savvy enough to find the real sender, that you forward the email to the
mail abuse mailbox for that domain (such as abuse@earthlink.net), so that they
are aware that someone is likely using their mail service to distribute viruses/trojan
horse software using someone else's name. Addendum: it's been pointed out that
it's also possible that someone has been hit with the KLEZ family of viruses,
and that they are unaware that their machine is sending out additional infected
files to/from various addy's on their hard drive. Regardless, always be very
careful when downloading file attachments.
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
</p>
<p><span class="headers">August 14, 2002 - Another Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>Well, the webserver is unwell this morning, so I'm not sure when folks will
get to see this update, but here's what we've got so far with regards to
tradeskills and the patch:
<ul>
  <li>the noodles recipe now works! Keep an eye on <a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerbaking">the
    baking forum</a> for any up-to-the-minute discoveries on the various yields,
    as well as recipes requiring noodles
  <li>casserole dish sketches now stack. This is indeed happy news for the
    potters that are making casserole dishes to go with our noodles
  <li>plains pebbles stack at last! Foragers around Norrath are heaving sighs of
    relief as their overloaded packs get a bit of relief
  <li>in other pack-happy news, black acrylia now stacks
  <li>the adding items to stacks issue that caused you to pick up the entire
    stack when trying to drop an item into the stack, has been fixed
  <li>the bazaar search function now lets you see an alphabetic listing of
    traders</li>
</ul>
<p>Other items with this patch include druid/wizzie ports from anywhere to
various locations on the moon, a fix to the tracking box, and much more. See <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/support/customer_service/cs_patch_message.jsp">the
complete patch message here</a>. Happy tradeskilling!
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
