<p><span class="headers">July 24, 2002 - Patch Day</span>
<p>
<p>Today's patch is quite large, so it will likely be a while before we catch
and mention everything in it that impacts tradeskills. While I sift through the
many posts on the subject, here are a few things of note:
<ul>
  <li>The new UI has been released, including the bazaar functionality. Remember
    that you must set "newui=TRUE" in your eqclient.ini file before
    you can buy <i>or</i> sell using the new bazaar trader functions.
  <li>The Jaggedpine zone has been released (it is an optional patch, so you
    must actively ask for it under the Advanced options when loading EQ). The
    baking forum already has a <a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerbaking.showMessage?topicID=1820.topic">thread
    started for new recipes and trivials</a> from this zone.
  <li>Stats on stat drinks are reported as working.
  <li>Faydwer was updated with quests for young adventurers. Information on the
    quests can be found in the Quests message board under the following threads:
    <a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm11.showMessage?topicID=871.topic">Felwithe
    Newbie Quests</a>, <a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm11.showMessage?topicID=870.topic">Kelethin
    Newbie Quests</a>, and <a href="http://pub126.ezboard.com/feqtraderscornerfrm11.showMessage?topicID=869.topic">Kaladim
    Newbie Quests</a>. I'll give it a day or two before I make up quests pages
    for all of these.
  <li>Cazic-Thule tailored items did <i>not</i> get an expected upgrade with
    this patch.</li>
</ul>
<p>That looks to be about it on the updates for today, other than the
decomissioning of the May 8 recipes page at long last. (All recipes stemming
from the May 8 patch should now be on their permanent recipes pages.)
</p>
<p>
<div align="right"><i>Created By: Niami Denmother&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</i></div><br>
