<p><span class="headers">July 15, 2002 - Happy Belated Anniversary to /gu comics!</span>
<p>
<p>I know I'm a tad slow, because this actually happened last week, but I'd like
to take a moment to wish <a href="http://www.gucomics.keenspace" target="_new">Woody
and his humorous comics of EQ life</a> a happy 2-year anniversary. I'm very
pleased that Woody has allowed me to display several of his tradeskill-related
comics around the EQTC site, and happy to see him still producing those
wonderful comics. Some days, we need to be able to find a giggle or three, and
his panels "do the trick."</p>
<p>In other news, Mennix of "<a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/dear_mennix.jsp" target="_new">Dear
Mennix</a>" fame has decided to turn the tables on some of the sites that
have traditionally cornered VI staff for interviews, and has started his own
interview series with various EQ "community leaders". Perhaps he
decided to start "easy" with a fellow halfling, or perhaps he's
getting even for a stray toe-fur comment, but it seems I'm <a href="http://eqlive.station.sony.com/community/articles.jsp?id=49593" target="_new">first
in the limelight</a>. Och! ;)</p>
</p>
